          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13032340/comment/15817037",
            "id": "15817037",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vrushalic",
              "name": "vrushalic",
              "key": "vrushalic",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10433",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10433",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10433",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10433"
              },
              "displayName": "Vrushali C",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "body": "In the context of retrieving information from the flow activity table, here is a suggestion that will help frameworks like Tez:\n\n- In the flow activity table (as well as flow run table), we should also store the framework type of the flow, for instance, for a job that runs as part of the Tez workflow, we should add in a column like \"type!tez\" and value could be null.\n- this will enable queries like which are the most recently run flows which have framework type of \"Tez\" on the flow activity table.\n\nOne flow can have multiple framework types, for instance, an oozie job can have pig and then hadoop map reduce. The flow will have three columns \"type!oozie\", \"type!pig\" , \"type!mr\". \n",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vrushalic",
              "name": "vrushalic",
              "key": "vrushalic",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10433",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10433",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10433",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10433"
              },
              "displayName": "Vrushali C",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "created": "2017-01-11T03:30:18.325+0000",
            "updated": "2017-01-11T03:30:18.325+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13032340/comment/15818964",
            "id": "15818964",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "Agreed we should hit the flow-activity table. Other tables don't have a strong time-range in the key and will result in very large scans.\n+1 for storing the framework types for a flow. From the HBase perspective we could make the value the count of the applications of that type in a flow, but that has two problems: increments aren't idempotent (in light of spooling and replay), and our plumbing would have to be adjusted. So probably we should just store 1 as the value and then use a SingleColumnValueExcludeFilter to return only those flows with the particular type having an activity in a day.\n\nThis does mean that we have to have the framework type present each time we insert a record into the flow activity table.\n",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2017-01-11T17:52:57.731+0000",
            "updated": "2017-01-11T17:52:57.731+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13032340/comment/15819113",
            "id": "15819113",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=varun_saxena",
              "name": "varun_saxena",
              "key": "varun_saxena",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Varun Saxena",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "Well, whatever you are asking for here would lead to a full table scan for Application table. And records won't be in order as well due to the structure of the row key.\nThis came up during the discussion on YARN-5585 as well I think and at that time I had suggested that if all you want is just a list of Application IDs', we can probably use App to flow table to show it.\nWould only App IDs' be enough or you need more metadata i.e. some other application attributes?\n\nFrankly, the intention of ATSv2 at the time of design was to model workflows i.e. let users drill down from flows to apps to generic entities. Whereas, what you want is application ID directly. Would it not be possible for Tez UI to follow the same order of flows->flowruns->apps (depending on the outcome of how we display flows in YARN-6027)?\nAs Tez executes the DAG within the scope of an application, its case is somewhat unique though.\n\nWe should, however, store app type as well, as others said.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=varun_saxena",
              "name": "varun_saxena",
              "key": "varun_saxena",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Varun Saxena",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "created": "2017-01-11T20:45:04.379+0000",
            "updated": "2017-01-11T20:45:04.379+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13032340/comment/15820029",
            "id": "15820029",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rohithsharma",
              "name": "rohithsharma",
              "key": "rohithsharma",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Rohith Sharma K S",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/New_York"
            },
            "body": "+1 for flow type which is very much necessary. \nThere are 2 pieces \n#  When a workflow is submitted by Oozie which has many actions(MR, Tez, Spak), then flow type should be Oozie. Always better to consider submitter as flow type. It can not be a Union of all applications type because each run can have different execution engine. \n# */apps* is also required because every execution framework has their own UI.(JHS for MR, Tez). These frameworks render entities of respective framework. Say, Oozie submits (MR,Tez) actions then Tez UI renders  DAG of Oozie Tez. And similarly, JHS renders job details of Oozie MR. Such cases, */apps* help to get those applications directly rather than going through flows.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rohithsharma",
              "name": "rohithsharma",
              "key": "rohithsharma",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Rohith Sharma K S",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/New_York"
            },
            "created": "2017-01-12T03:21:59.261+0000",
            "updated": "2017-01-12T03:21:59.261+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13032340/comment/15822243",
            "id": "15822243",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "Note that we've slowly drifted in terminology and I think in our understanding of what is proposed by [~vrushalic].\nVrushali suggested to add the existing framework types for each application in a flow-run to the flow run and flow activity tables. Each and every framework that happened to have an application in a flow run (and on that specific date for the flow activity table) would be marked as a special column.\n\nWe're not discussing adding a new single flow type for a flow. The types are simply the \"enumeration\" of framework types for each app in the flow.\n\nTherefore Tez, MR, Spark and all other framework specific UIs would then pass in their own framework type to the queries for flow runs and flow activity and retrieve only those flow runs which contain an application of their type. When they then retrieve applications, an additional filtering would be needed.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2017-01-13T19:42:58.131+0000",
            "updated": "2017-01-13T19:42:58.131+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13032340/comment/16396232",
            "id": "16396232",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=haibochen",
              "name": "haibochen",
              "key": "haibochen",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Haibo Chen",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "This showed up while I was exploring replacing JHS with python scripts (will be YARN UI2-like thing) + ATSv2. This is no good story in ATSv2 that supports client retrieval of all jobs (flow->flow run-> apps does not work without user id).\r\n\r\nI think in MR's use case, a limit param on the query would be good enough.\u00a0 The application id, in YARN's case, contains cluster timestamp + the current app counter that increments each time. We may be able to leverage that information to support time-range queries as well.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=haibochen",
              "name": "haibochen",
              "key": "haibochen",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
